The paper focuses on developing a system to detect student engagement in e-learning scenarios using information from a web-camera. This involves analyzing facial emotions, eye tracking, and head movement, which falls under the sub-categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions using natural language processing techniques to analyze chat logs, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL), and using multimedia data, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
